HEADWORD: Unbank
<hw>Un*bank"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>bank</ets>.]</ety> <def>To remove a bank from; to
open by, or as if by, the removal of a bank.</def> <rj><au>H.
Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

